@HD2 New Briefs head;Modi picks Varanasi
@BT New Screen/briefs Text - no indent;India's opposition leader Narendra Modi, frontrunner to be the country's next prime minister after elections starting on April 7, will contest the polls from the Hindu holy city of Varanasi.
"Grateful to the party for giving me opportunity to contest the election from the holy city of Varanasi! An honour to contest from Varanasi," Modi tweeted.
The move is part of the Bharatiya Janata Party's tactics to win the critical northern battleground state of Uttar Pradesh, where the Hindu temple city of Varanasi, home to around 1.4 million people, is located.
